<h2 id="azimuth-security">Azimuth Security</h2>
<p>Azimuth Security is an Australian cybersecurity firm best known as a "hack for hire" group that creates hacking tools, including those capable of breaking into iPhones. The company has gained recognition for its "artisanal" approach to developing exploits to craft precise and effective solutions. Azimuth's work has been utilized by law enforcement and government agencies, often in high-profile cases requiring advanced technical capabilities. In 2018, it was acquired by U.S. defense contractor L3Harris.</p>
