<h2 id="berico-technologies">Berico Technologies</h2>
<p>Berico Technologies provided analytics solutions and surveillance technologies for government clients, including social media analysis for intelligence purposes. Patrick Ryan, who worked at Berico as a data mining expert, was involved in a proposal aimed at implementing real-time surveillance of politically active individuals and groups in the USA. In partnership with Palantir Technologies and HBGary Federal, the proposal would have included spying on the families of prominent Democratic activists and planting fabricated documents within labor unions to undermine their credibility. Novetta, Inc., a portfolio company of The Carlyle Group, acquired Berico Technologies in November 2018 for an undisclosed sum. Novetta was then acquired by Accenture Federal in 2021.</p>
