<h2 id="cyberglobes">Cyberglobes</h2>
<p>Cyberglobes, an Israeli open-source intelligence (OSINT) firm, has established itself as a prominent exporter of intelligence solutions despite facing bans from platforms like Facebook due to its spying activities. Led by Pinhas (aka Pini) Kleiner, the company has been expanding its global footprint, recently showcasing its social network monitoring tools at the Digipol policing and defense fair in Hyderabad, India. Cyberglobes has a history in the Indian market, having demonstrated its solutions to Indian police forces as early as 2019. It has also been pitching its social network surveillance technologies to the United Arab Emirates.</p>
