<h2 id="dataflow-security">Dataflow Security</h2>
<p>Dataflow Security is an Italian firm that sells exploits to European and Middle Eastern intelligence agencies. The company is a regular presence at industry events like ISS World and has recruited talent from NSO Group.</p>
<p>The firm was founded in 2019 and is headed by Italian national Luca Todesco, a prominent zero-day tracker. In 2020, one of Todesco's iPhone attack techniques, which he shared publicly with Chinese contacts, was reportedly used by China to spy on the Uyghur community, as documented by Forbes.</p>
