<h2 id="digital-receiver-technology">Digital Receiver Technology</h2>
<p>Digital Receiver Technology (DRT), a subsidiary of Boeing since its acquisition in 2008, is a developer of surveillance and wireless communication tools, including IMSI catchers - devices used for intercepting mobile communications. These tools are widely utilized by intelligence and defense agencies for monitoring and gathering data. The company's clients include the U.S Department of Defense, U.S Department of the Army, and the U.S. Marshals Service.</p>
<p>In 2024, DRT was acquired from Boeing by Thales Defense and Security Inc (TDSI), a subsidiary of Thales.</p>
