<h2 id="dream-security">Dream Security</h2>
<p>Dream Security is a company co-founded by Shalev Hulio, the former CEO of NSO Group, an Israeli technology firm known for developing sophisticated surveillance tools, including the Pegasus spyware. The other co-founders include Sebastian Kurz, the former chancellor of Austria, and Michael Eisenberg, an Israeli American venture capitalist who is also a general partner of Aleph, a Tel-Aviv-based venture capital firm which participated in funding for Dream. </p>
<p>As of early 2025, the company claimed $130 million in annual sales, primarily from government agencies.</p>
