<h2 id="echo-on-technologies">Echo-On Technologies</h2>
<p>Echo-On Technologies was founded in 2018 as a subsidiary of the Israeli firm Rayzone Group. Its primary product, Echo, is a surveillance tool designed to exploit vulnerabilities in telecommunications systems like SS7.  It enables capabilities such as real-time location tracking, call interception, and SMS message retrieval. Echo is marketed primarily to governments and law enforcement agencies for intelligence gathering and surveillance purposes. It has reportedly been used in Mexico. The purchase was made via Neolinx, an intermediary in Mexico used to purchase surveillance equipment.</p>
