<h2 id="facefirst">FaceFirst</h2>
<p>FaceFirst, also known as Airborne Biometrics, is a developer of facial recognition and surveillance technologies, providing automated face-matching systems for use in retail, airports, stadiums, military bases and at border checkpoints. </p>
<p>Its facial recognition technology has increasingly been deployed in retail stores without customer knowledge or consent. The system scans shoppers' faces as they enter stores, comparing them to databases of "dishonest customers" or "known shoplifters." The system also delivers customizable alerts and notifications to any device or workstation upon detecting a person of interest. The company claims to offer military-grade facial identification that seamlessly connects to a large central database tailored to the specific needs of the end user.</p>
<p>In 2022, FaceFirst welcomed Edwin Coello, a former leader of the NYPD Real Time Crime Center, to its team.</p>
