<h2 id="faicetech">FaiceTech</h2>
<p>FaiceTech is a UK-based developer of facial recognition technology. It has been implicated in helping Hikvision, a Chinese security camera giant, circumvent international sanctions over its involvement in surveillance and human rights abuses in Xinjiang. Hikvision advertised ethnicity recognition features in marketing brochures, claiming collaboration with FaiceTech. Following an investigation, Hikvision removed promotional materials referencing FaiceTech.</p>
