<h2 id="fiberhome">FiberHome</h2>
<p>FiberHome, officially known as Nanjing FiberHome StarrySky Communication Development Company Ltd., develops spyware for use by the Chinese authorities. Its Fengcai app is forcibly installed on tourists' smartphones at border crossings in the East Turkistan (renamed Xinjiang by China) region. This spyware collects extensive personal data, including text messages, contacts, call logs, calendar entries, and installed apps, and transmits it to remote servers for analysis. The app also scans for content flagged as suspicious, such as religious materials, writings in Arabic, or documents related to the Dalai Lama, among other flagged items.</p>
