<h2 id="frontiir">Frontiir</h2>
<p>Frontiir is a Myanmar-based internet service provider (ISP) that has been facilitating digital surveillance for the country's military junta. The company operates under the Myanmar Net brand, providing internet services to millions of users. Investigations have revealed that Frontiir hosts surveillance equipment developed by Geedge Networks, a Chinese cybersecurity firm founded by Fang Binxing, known as the "father" of China's Great Firewall. This equipment reportedly enables the interception and decryption of web traffic, blocking of websites, and prevention of Virtual Private Network (VPN) usage, thereby restricting access to uncensored information. Frontiir's Yangon data center has been identified as housing this surveillance technology.</p>
<details class="tip">
