<h2 id="geofeedia">Geofeedia</h2>
<p>Geofeedia was hired by California police departments after pitching its ability to identify civil rights protesters, according to an American Civil Liberties Union report. Without public hearings or civilian oversight, the Oakland Police Department has used it to conduct surveillance on large public gatherings, possibly including political protests.</p>
