<h2 id="geolitica">Geolitica</h2>
<p>Geolitica, formerly known as PredPol, short for "Predictive Policing," is a software company that claims to use historical crime data to predict where crimes are likely to occur. Its surveillance capabilities rely on analyzing past crime reports, including time, location, and type of crime, to generate "hot spots" for law enforcement to monitor. This data-driven approach enabled police departments, such as the LAPD, to direct patrols and resources to specific areas flagged by the system. PredPol however specifically targeted Black and brown neighborhoods in the U.S, and its algorithms created often false and misleading data that intensified surveillance in these communities.</p>
