<h2 id="inmarket">InMarket</h2>
<p>InMarket is a location data broker that has been involved in tracking and selling users' precise location information collected through smartphone apps. The company operates by gathering location data from mobile applications and then selling this information to various clients. In early 2024, InMarket faced regulatory enforcement action from the Federal Trade Commission, which placed restrictions on the company's ability to sell location data.</p>
