<h2 id="intelos">Intelos</h2>
<p>Intelos, also known as Adhoc, is an Israeli firm specializing in geolocation tracking and spyware distribution through online advertising. The company has established a significant presence in Asia, particularly with its operations in Hong Kong. Founded by Eric Banoun, co-founder of Israeli spyware firm Circles, and Roy Shloman, a former partner at surveillance firm Senpai Technologies, Intelos is also partially owned by Hong Kong-based Colibri Technologies, which Banoun founded in 2017. Shloman's Senpai is best known for helping Malaysia's government spy on opposition.</p>
