<h2 id="invasys">Invasys</h2>
<p>Founded in 2017 in Brno, Czech Republic, by former Norwegian government security adviser Kyrre Sletsjoe, Invasys is a discreet developer of surveillance technologies. The company develops ways for intelligence services to bypass smartphone encryption and improve their interception capabilities. Building on Sletsjoe's previous venture, Cepia Technologies, Invasys exploits vulnerabilities in GSM communication protocols, particularly the widely used A5 encryption.</p>
<p>Invasys often markets its surveillance and interception products in trade shows like ISS, IPAS and IDEX.</p>
