<h2 id="jouav">Jouav</h2>
<p>Jouav is a Chinese manufacturer of aerial surveillance technologies. Its aircraft, including the CW‑15, CW‑25E, CW‑30E, and CW‑80E models, are designed with vertical take‑off and landing capabilities and can operate for up to eight hours with a range of roughly 200 km. These drones include features such as high‑resolution EO/IR cameras and LiDAR sensors for real-time surveillance and automated tracking of targets. They are typically used by Chinese authorities for border monitoring. </p>
<p>Its founders, Ren Bin and Wang Chen, were previously officers in the People's Liberation Army's General Armaments Department.</p>
