<h2 id="kospy">KoSpy</h2>
<p>KoSpy is a malicious spyware attributed to the North Korean state-sponsored hacking group APT37 (also known as Reaper). This sophisticated malware was found on the Google Play Store, embedded in seemingly legitimate Android apps. KoSpy is designed to covertly collect sensitive user data, including including SMS text messages, call logs, the device’s location data, files and folders on the device, user-entered keystrokes, Wi-Fi network details, and a list of installed apps, while operating undetected. 
KoSpy can also record audio, take pictures with the phone’s cameras, and capture screenshots of the screen in use.</p>
