<h2 id="linchpin-labs">Linchpin Labs</h2>
<p>Linchpin Labs is a software development and cybersecurity firm with a history of working with government clients, reportedly selling zero-day exploits and other tools to intelligence agencies, including those within the Five Eyes alliance. It frequently collaborates with its partner company, Azimuth Security, to provide such hacking capabilities to government entities. In 2018, it was acquired by U.S. defense contractor L3Harris.</p>
