<h2 id="narus">Narus</h2>
<p>Narus, a subsidiary of Boeing, has sold its NarusInsight technology, used for mass surveillance of internet traffic, to several countries with known human rights violations, including Saudi Arabia and Egypt. Capabilities include Deep Packet Inspection equipment (DPI), a content-filtering technology that allows network managers to inspect, track and target content from users of the Internet and mobile phones, as it passes through routers on the information superhighway. Narus was was founded in 1997 by Israeli "security experts" to create and sell mass surveillance systems for governments and large corporate clients.</p>
