<h2 id="netsweeper">Netsweeper</h2>
<p>Netsweeper, a Canadian company that develops internet filtering technology, enables internet censorship and surveillance in various countries. The company's software is used to block access to content deemed politically or socially sensitive, such as websites related to political dissent, religious topics, independent media, and LGBTQ+ rights. Netsweeper's technology employs automated mechanisms to filter content across multiple categories, which can be customized by clients, including governments and ISPs. Its tools include onGuard, which monitors student activity in real time, tracking desktop content, internet usage, and user-submitted data.</p>
