<h2 id="novispy">NoviSpy</h2>
<p>NoviSpy is a spyware discovered by Amnesty International. It was found on a Serbian journalist's phone, reportedly installed after the device was unlocked using a Cellebrite tool. NoviSpy operates through two applications, NoviSpyAdmin and NoviSpyAccess, which exploit Android's accessibility services to perform extensive surveillance. Its capabilities include capturing screenshots, exfiltrating files, tracking location, and remotely activating the device's microphone and camera. Installed via the Android Debug Bridge (adb), NoviSpy has been in development since at least 2018.</p>
