<h2 id="pathar">PathAR</h2>
<p>PathAR is a technology company specializing in social media monitoring analytics for intelligence gathering, with its primary product, Dunami, being used by U.S government agencies like the FBI and U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP). Dunami mines data from platforms such as Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram to create detailed profiles of users and map networks of association. </p>
<p>The Chicago Public Schools (CPS) received a $2.2 million grant in 2014 from the U.S. Department of Justice’s Comprehensive School Safety Initiative. Part of the grant was allocated to hire two intelligence analysts and to purchase Dunami, which was then used to monitor students' public social media activity. The program initially targeted 16 schools and later expanded to 24 schools, covering approximately 25,000 students.</p>
<p>The company is backed by In-Q-Tel, the CIA's venture capital arm.</p>
