<h2 id="pelco">Pelco</h2>
<p>Californian company Pelco uses monitoring equipment by Israeli company Vigilant Technologies to implement one of the largest digital monitoring systems in the world via a collaboration with NYPD in the U.S. Pelco was acquired by Schneider Electric, a French multinational corporation, in 2007. Later, in 2019, Pelco was sold by Schneider Electric to Transom Capital Group. Pelco was eventually acquired by Motorola Solutions in 2020 and remains its current owner.</p>
<p>Pelco cooperates with Dahua Technology, whose tools are used by the authorities in China to track, monitor and target Uyghurs.</p>
