<h2 id="prelysis">Prelysis</h2>
<p>Prelysis provides Wi-Fi interception systems for surveillance purposes. Based in Israel, it also has a presence in Cyprus, where they have obtained export licenses for the sale of their monitoring tools to non-EU countries. It is headed by Israeli citizen Kobi Naveh, who worked for worked for the Israeli company Verint until 2014. Verint is also the company that acquired the Cyprus-registered surveillance company UTX Technologies. Bangladesh’s internal intelligence agency, or NSI, bought a system for intercepting Wi-Fi communications from the company.</p>
