<h2 id="rank-one-computing">Rank One Computing</h2>
<p>Rank One Computing (ROC) is a U.S.-based provider of facial recognition and multimodal biometric technologies, used by government, defense, and law enforcement agencies. Capabilities of their products include facial recognition, fingerprint, and iris recognition, alongside AI-driven video analytics. They also provide license plate recognition tools. The company has been linked to bias and errors in facial recognition, with studies showing higher error rates for individuals with darker skin tones.</p>
