<h2 id="techops-specialty-vehicles">TechOps Specialty Vehicles</h2>
<p>TechOps Specialty Vehicles (TOSV) is a company that builds custom vehicles for law enforcement, outfitting them with various surveillance technologies. It supplied U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) with vehicles equipped with cell-site simulators, commonly known as fake cell towers or "stingrays." This enables law enforcement agencies to intercept cellular signals and track mobile phones by mimicking legitimate cell towers, forcing nearby devices to connect to them.</p>
<p>The company is headquartered in Stevensville, Maryland. The company also maintains sales locations in Denver, Colorado, and Whitefish, Montana.</p>
