<h2 id="vastech">VASTech</h2>
<p>In a 2016 pamphlet produced by VASTech SA Pty Ltd., the company outlines its current capabilities for governments, militaries, and law enforcement agencies around the world, claiming it can conduct “passive detection” of communications transmitted from satellites, fix-and-mobile phones, and fiber optic cable. One of its systems is called Zebra. VASTech says Zebra offers "access to high volumes of information generated via telecommunication services for the purposes of analysis and investigation". It has been designed to "intercept all content and metadata of voice, SMS, email and fax communications on the connected network, creating a rich repository of information".</p>
