<h2 id="zencity">Zencity</h2>
<p>Zencity is an Israeli data analytics company that helps local governments monitor public sentiment by analyzing social media, message boards, local news, and other public data sources. Serving over 200 agencies across the United States, its platform is used by U.S cities like Phoenix, New Orleans, and Pittsburgh to track public reactions to topics. It also enables police agencies to track negative sentiment toward law enforcement without residents' knowledge or consent. </p>
<p>The lack of public oversight in contracts with Zencity, often approved without city council input, has led to criticism that usage of the tool prioritizes surveillance over genuine community engagement.</p>
